<subSubSection id="C327657AFFC9FFA7FF7878C69EE2FAAF" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8236F1FFC9FFA7FF7878C69E48FB47" blockId="6.[151,1437,258,1398]" box="[199,1320,1158,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis id="B949EAE3FFC9FFA7FF7878C69A31FB46" bold="true" box="[199,337,1159,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Etymology:</emphasis>
Dedicated to Gloria Ariza, mantid specialist at the Universidad del Tolima (
<collectingCountry id="F32A7661FFC9FFA7FB1878C79E7CFB47" box="[1191,1308,1158,1182]" name="Colombia" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Colombia</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8236F1FFC9FFA7FF7878EB9A17FB1A" blockId="6.[151,1437,258,1398]" box="[199,375,1194,1219]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis id="B949EAE3FFC9FFA7FF7878EB9A17FB1A" bold="true" box="[199,375,1194,1219]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D72FFC9FFA7FF7878EB9A41FB1A" box="[199,289,1194,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Markia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hystrix">Hystrix</taxonomicName>
Group
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8236F1FFC9FFA7FF78788F9EE2FAAF" blockId="6.[151,1437,258,1398]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
The species of this group are medium-sized (
<quantity id="4CC59B14FFC9FFA7FD7A788F9824FB3F" box="[709,836,1230,1254]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" metricValueMax="5.4" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" unit="mm" value="52.0" valueMax="54.0" valueMin="50.0">50–54 mm</quantity>
). Pronotal spines are enlarged; at least the metazonal spine is distinctly longer than the fastigium. Spines of the legs are elongated, outer margin of hind femur with seven or eight spines projecting towards the sides, the sixth spine being usually strongly raised beyond the dorsal margin. Branches of the cerci are armed with ventral or apical denticulations. The known distribution of this group is mostly Central American, with one species in the Colombian Pacific coast and possibly extending to 
<collectingCountry id="F32A7661FFC9FFA7FAA1791F9E1EFAAF" box="[1310,1406,1374,1398]" name="Ecuador" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
